For handling asynchronous exceptions and bad stack traces, checkout the "trycatch" module on npm, <a href="http://github.com/crabdude/trycatch" rel="nofollow">http://github.com/crabdude/trycatch</a> . It's an asynchronous try catch.<p><pre><code>  trycatch(function(){
    process.nextTick(function() {
      throw new Error("This will be caught.");
    });
  }, function(e) {
    console.log(e.stack);
  });
</code></pre>
I also integrated it into the step module to create "stepup" which adds error coalescing, <a href="http://github.com/crabdude/stepup" rel="nofollow">http://github.com/crabdude/stepup</a> .
